The main road between landlockedZambia and the Tanzanian port of Dar es Salaam is to berehabilitated at a cost of 109 mln dlrs, starting in December,Willie Lyatu, the project coordinator in the Tanzanian Ministryof Communications, said.    The road runs parallel to the Chinese-built Tazara,(Tanzania-Zambia) railway and is in bad condition.    Lyatu said the government was currently evaluating 52 bidsby international contractors to rehabilitate 293.5 km of theasphalt highway and 800 km of other trunk roads with a gravelsurface.    The final list of contractors would be issued by the WorldBank, the project's main sponsor, at the end of April, headded.    The World Bank is contributing 50 mln dlrs to the project,which is also being financed by the African Development Bank,Norway and Denmark. Reuter&#3;